data.name: comboOptimizeType.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies if optimization is to be done either for all transitions in each precursor totaled or for each transition separately

data.name: cbUseOptimized.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, the any measured CE or DP optimization values will be used to select the value exported in methods and transition lists. The value producing the maximum total peak area will be chosen.

data.name: comboDeclusterPotential.ToolTip
data.value: A linear equation used to predict the optimal declustering potential (DP) for each precursor from its mass-to-charge ratio. Isotope labeled peptides use the predicted DP for the unlabeled form. (AB instruments only)

data.name: comboCollisionEnergy.ToolTip
data.value: A linear equation used to predict the optimal collsion energy (CE) for each precursor from its mass-to-charge ratio. Isotope labeled peptides use the predicted CE for the unlabeled form.

data.name: comboIonMass.ToolTip
data.value: Molecular mass calculation strategy (monoisotopic or average) to use in calculating all product ion masses

data.name: comboPrecursorMass.ToolTip
data.value: Molecular mass calculation strategy (monoisotopic or average) to use in calculating all precursor masses

data.name: cbExclusionUseDIAWindow.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, the precursor exclusion window is taken from the Full-Scan settings instead of being symmetric around the precursor m/z. This is recommended for DIA/SWATH data.

data.name: textPeptideIonTypes.ToolTip
data.value: A list of comma separated product ion types (a, b, c, x, y, z, z., z', p for precursor) to use for calculating potential product ions. z. and z' stand for z+1 radical ion and z+2 ion. Those are usually found in ExD experiments. Alternatively, z* and z" can be used.

data.name: btnEditSpecialTransitions.ToolTip
data.value: Edit the list of available special product ions

data.name: listAlwaysAdd.ToolTip
data.value: Set of special product ions to measure when present, even outside the filtered range

data.name: comboRangeFrom.ToolTip
data.value: Starting product ion for a filtered range of ions

data.name: comboRangeTo.ToolTip
data.value: End point for a filtered range of product ions

data.name: textPeptidePrecursorCharges.ToolTip
data.value: A list of comma separated charge states to use for calculating precursor mass-to-charge ratios

data.name: textPeptideIonCharges.ToolTip
data.value: A list of comma separated charge states to use for calculating product ion mass-to-charge ratios

data.name: textSmallMoleculeFragmentAdducts.ToolTip
data.value:
Adducts:
Ion formulas may contain an adduct description using the defacto standard notation as seen at http://fiehnlab.ucdavis.edu/staff/kind/Metabolomics/MS-Adduct-Calculator (e.g. "C47H51NO14[M+IsoProp+H]").
When only the ion charge is known (often the case with fragments) charge-only adducts such as "[M+]" (z=1), "[M-]" (z=-1), "[M+3]" (z=3), etc., may be used.
Multipliers (e.g. the "2" in "[2M+K]") and isotope labels (e.g. the "2Cl37" in "[M2Cl37+H]") are supported.
Recognized adduct components include normal chemical symbols and: ACN (C2H3N), DMSO (C2H6OS), FA (CH2O2), Hac (CH3COOH), TFA (C2HF3O2), IsoProp (C3H8O), MeOH (CH3OH), Cl37 (Cl'), Br81 (Br'), H2 (H'), C13 (C'), N15 (N'), O17 (O"), O18 (O')
Charge states are inferred from the presence of these adduct components: H (+1), K (+1), Na (+1), Li (+1), Br (-1), Cl (-1), F (-1), CH3COO (-1), HCOO (-1), NH4 (+1)

data.name: textSmallMoleculeIonTypes.ToolTip
data.value: A list of comma separated product ion types (f for fragment, p for precursor) to use in filtering spectral libraries etc.

data.name: textExclusionWindow.ToolTip
data.value: A m/z window around the precursor m/z within which transitions are excluded, or blank. A window of 20 will exclude all transitions within 10 on either side of the precursor m/z.

data.name: cbAutoSelect.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, tranitions are automatically chosen for peptides using specified filter and library settings. Otherwise, all transition selection must be done by manual document editing.

data.name: textMinIonCount.ToolTip
data.value: Pick precursors with at least this many transitions

data.name: radioAllAndFiltered.Text
data.value: From filtered ion charges and types pl&us filtered product ions

data.name: radioAllAndFiltered.ToolTip
data.value: Apply only the ion charges and types from the Filter tab to the selection of MS/MS peaks matching ions for ranking, but also add all product ions matching the full filter, if they are not found in the library

data.name: radioFiltered.ToolTip
data.value: Apply parameters from the Filter tab to the selection of MS/MS peaks matching ions for ranking

data.name: radioAll.ToolTip
data.value: Apply only the ion charges and types from the Filter tab to the selection of MS/MS peaks matching ions for ranking

data.name: textIonCount.ToolTip
data.value: Pick this many transitions for each precursor by library spectrum peak intensity ranking

data.name: textTolerance.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum delta allowed when matching predicted product ion m/z values with measured MS/MS spectral library peak m/z values

data.name: cbLibraryPick.Text
data.value: If a library &spectrum is available, pick its most intense ions

data.name: cbLibraryPick.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, the transition filter is based on MS/MS spectral library peaks whenever peptides are matched to library spectrum.

data.name: cbxTriggeredAcquisition.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates that there may be large gaps in the retention times when spectra were acquired for certain analytes. Peaks will be truncated to not overlap with these gaps and background subtraction will not be performed.

data.name: textMaxInclusions.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum number of inclusion windows measured by the target instrument during multiplexed scanning.

data.name: textMaxTime.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum time allowed in chromatograms regardless of how they were acquired. Setting this can save memory and disk space that might be used on uninteresting parts of the gradient.

data.name: textMinTime.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum time allowed in chromatograms regardless of how they were acquired. Setting this can save memory and disk space that might be used on uninteresting parts of the gradient.

data.name: cbDynamicMinimum.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, minimum m/z value for product ions is calculate dynamically from the precursor m/z using a specific equation provided by Thermo-Scientific for LTQ instruments

data.name: textMaxTrans.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum total number of transitions measurable by the target instrument in a single injection or blank if no maximum applies

data.name: textMzMatchTolerance.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum delta for matching instrument method transition m/z values with predicted transition m/z values. (Applies only to SRM and targeted-MS/MS data.)

data.name: textMaxMz.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum measurable m/z value for the target instrument

data.name: textMinMz.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum measurable m/z value for the target instrument
